title: Cheryl and Liam Payne remain silent amidst fan speculation the star is 'in labour'
text:
Celebs Cheryl and Liam Payne remain silent amidst fan speculation the star is 'in labour' The One Direction star's fans have gone into meltdown on Twitter - but there's no word from Cheryl and Liam Share Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now What we've seen so far of Liam and Cheryl's baby Share this video Get celebs updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
Cheryl and Liam Payne appear to be ignoring suggestions the star is "in labour". 
One Direction star Liam flew back from Los Angeles this week in order to be by his girlfriends side, and his return got fans speculating that he may be about to become a father. 
Cheryl hasn't posted anything on Instagram for five weeks, which was already setting alarm bells for fans. But with Liam racing back to England, fans went into overdrive. 
Fans rushed to social media yesterday to speculate on his reason for making a swift return. Fans have sparked rumours (Photo: ITV) Liam has returned to the UK (Photo: Getty Images Europe) 
"Hold up, Cheryl is having the baby NOW?” wrote one excited fan. 
As added: "Cheryl’s super baby is coming.” 
Despite the wild speculation, both Cheryl and Liam have yet to break their silence over the claims. 
Liam's been in Los Angeles working on his debut solo album, which is due for release later this year. 
A source said recently: “Cheryl has been incredibly supportive of Liam and his music. She really wants him to do well, she knows what is like to have a solo career and how hard it is breaking out on your own. 
“They are both very excited about his career and of course about their new arrival. It’s a very happy time for both of them.” 
Cheryl and Liam, who have never publicly confirmed news they're expecting a child, just celebrated their first anniversary together. Liam's pal spoke about the news recently (Photo: Getty) 
Liam's former bandmate confirmed the news recently however when he spoke about his excitement. 
“I’m looking forward to it,” he told the Daily Star. 
“Liam hasn’t said he’s nervous but I’m sure he is. I bet he can’t wait as well. It is a very exciting thing in your life.”
